hands_on_practices.solution:
The fold enrichment at a locus is defined as
$$
\text{FE}=\frac{\left(\frac{\text{reads at locus in ChIP}}{\text{total reads in ChIP}}\right)}{\left(\frac{\text{reads at locus in Input}}{\text{total reads in Input}}\right)}.
$$
For the Untreated batch, using $r_{\text{ChIP}}=50$, $N_{\text{ChIP}}=20\times 10^{6}$, $r_{\text{Input}}=10$, and $N_{\text{Input}}=25\times 10^{6}$,
$$
\text{FE}_{\text{U}}=\frac{\frac{50}{20\times 10^{6}}}{\frac{10}{25\times 10^{6}}}
=\frac{50}{20\times 10^{6}}\cdot\frac{25\times 10^{6}}{10}
=\frac{50}{20}\cdot\frac{25}{10}
=\frac{5}{2}\cdot\frac{5}{2}
=\frac{25}{4} = 6.25.
$$
For the Treated batch, using $r_{\text{ChIP}}=1200$, $N_{\text{ChIP}}=22\times 10^{6}$, $r_{\text{Input}}=11$, and $N_{\text{Input}}=28\times 10^{6}$,
$$
\text{FE}_{\text{T}}=\frac{\frac{1200}{22\times 10^{6}}}{\frac{11}{28\times 10^{6}}}
=\frac{1200}{22}\cdot\frac{28}{11}
=\frac{600}{11}\cdot\frac{28}{11}
=\frac{16800}{121}.
$$
The requested ratio of Treated to Untreated fold enrichment is
$$
R=\frac{\text{FE}_{\text{T}}}{\text{FE}_{\text{U}}}
=\frac{\frac{16800}{121}}{\frac{25}{4}}
=\frac{16800}{121}\cdot\frac{4}{25}
=\frac{67200}{3025}
=\frac{2688}{121}\approx 22.214876\ldots
$$
Rounded to three significant figures, this is $22.2$.
